==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Hot-headed
<hw>Hot"-head`ed</hw>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>quickly and easily aroused to
anger; fiery; violent; rash; hasty; impetuous; vehement; <as>as, a
<ex>hot-headed</ex> commander</as>.</def> <wns>[wns=1]</wns>
<rj><au>Macaulay.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> choleric, irascible, hotheaded, hot-tempered,
quick-tempered, short-tempered.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>hotheaded</ent>⟦br⟧
